# WHAT IT IS
#   `signls` is a **terminal-native generative MIDI sequencer**
#   that takes the spatial-grid livecoding metaphor of Hundred
#   Rabbits' ORCA (the influential 2D cellular-automaton
#   livecoding programming language at hundredrabbits.itch.io)
#   and refines it specifically for MIDI sequencing:
#
#     ‚Ä¢ The screen is a 2D grid (configurable dimensions per
#       bank).  Each cell can hold a typed "operator" ‚Äî a single-
#       character glyph that defines what happens when the beat
#       pulses through that cell.
#
#     ‚Ä¢ Operators include note triggers (with configurable
#       pitch / velocity / duration / probability), directional
#       routers that redirect the beat in cardinal directions,
#       arithmetic operators that mutate notes as they pass
#       through, random-walk operators, conditional gates,
#       multi-channel splitters, drum-machine triggers, MIDI
#       CC emitters, MIDI program-change emitters, and SysEx
#       template emitters.
#
#     ‚Ä¢ Multiple grids (`bank.json` stores them all; switch
#       between active grids interactively).  Each grid has its
#       own tempo + key signature + scale-quantization rules +
#       per-channel MIDI device mapping.
#
#     ‚Ä¢ Per-keyboard-layout key bindings ‚Äî the `--keyboard`
#       flag selects between QWERTY, QWERTY-MAC, AZERTY (the
#       French keyboard layout), and AZERTY-MAC.
#
#     ‚Ä¢ Outputs MIDI via the gomidi/midi/v2 driver to any
#       OS-attached MIDI device (Linux ALSA Sequencer + JACK,
#       macOS CoreMIDI, Windows WinMM, JACK MIDI on any
#       platform).
#
#   The UI is fully terminal-based ‚Äî runs over `ssh` to a
#   headless machine, integrates with tmux, doesn't need an X
#   server or wayland compositor, and uses the same charm
#   bubbletea TUI framework that powers gum / glow / charm /
#   skate / vhs / sequin and dozens of other modern terminal
#   tools.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from main.go stdlib `flag`
#                       declarations;  extracted via
#                       raw.githubusercontent.com fetch of
#                       main.go)
#
#   signls [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -h, -help                      Show usage (auto-generated
#                                    by Go's stdlib `flag`
#                                    package)
#     -version                       Print current version (the
#                                    embedded `VERSION` file's
#                                    contents, baked in via
#                                    `//go:embed`)
#     -config <PATH>                 Config file to load or
#                                    create
#                                    [default: config.json]
#     -bank <PATH>                   Bank file to store grids
#                                    [default: default.json]
#     -keyboard <LAYOUT>             Keyboard layout
#                                    [values: qwerty, qwerty-mac,
#                                             azerty, azerty-mac]
#     -debug                         Enable debug mode (writes
#                                    `debug.log` in the working
#                                    directory)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `emprcl/signls` declares a **direct** dependency on
#   `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2 v2.2.19` in its `go.mod` (verified
#   via `gh api repos/emprcl/signls/contents/go.mod`).  The
#   `main.go` source imports `"signls/midi"` (an internal
#   wrapper that fronts gomidi/midi/v2 directly with the typed
#   `midi.New()` /  `midi.Close()` driver lifecycle).
#
#   `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2` is **THE canonical Go MIDI
#   library** ‚Äî Marc Ren√© Arns's reference cross-platform Go
#   MIDI I/O implementation, the de-facto Go MIDI dependency
#   on pkg.go.dev with ~150 dependent projects.  Ships as a
#   multi-package module:
#
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2`              the core API
#       (typed `Message`, `NoteOn(ch, key, vel)`,
#       `NoteOff(ch, key)`, `Pitchbend(ch, val)`, `PolyAfter
#       Touch(ch, key, pressure)`, `AfterTouch(ch, pressure)`,
#       `ProgramChange(ch, prog)`, `ControlChange(ch, cc, val)`,
#       `SysEx(data)`, `MTC(quarterFrame)`, `Stop()`, `Start()`,
#       `Continue()`, `Clock()`, `Reset()`, `ActiveSensing()`,
#       `TuneRequest()`, `SongPositionPointer(pos)`,
#       `SongSelect(song)` typed message builders + matching
#       receiver discriminators)
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2/drivers/rtmididrv`  RtMidi
#       binding (the canonical C++ RtMidi driver wrapped in
#       cgo) ‚Äî runs everywhere
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2/drivers/portmididrv`
#       PortMidi binding (the alternative C library wrapped)
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2/drivers/midicatdrv`
#       midicat command-line binary driver (no cgo ‚Äî uses
#       midicat subprocess + stdin/stdout MIDI bytes)
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2/drivers/testdrv`
#       in-memory test driver
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2/drivers/alsadrv`
#       Linux-native pure-Go ALSA Sequencer driver
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2/drivers/webmididrv`
#       Web MIDI API driver (compile to wasm32-js for
#       browser-side Go MIDI tools)
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2/smf`           Standard MIDI
#       File (SMF) reader + writer with typed `Track`,
#       `MetaEvent`, `TempoMap`, `TimeSignature`, `KeySignature`
#       primitives ‚Äî read + write `.mid` files
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2/sequencer`     a typed
#       playback sequencer engine
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2/sequencer/transformer`
#       typed event transformers (transpose, quantize,
#       channel-remap, randomize)
#     ‚Ä¢ `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2/sequencer/scheduler`
#       typed event scheduler primitives
#
#   It exposes:
#
#     ‚Ä¢ Typed `midi.InPorts() []drivers.In` /
#       `midi.OutPorts() []drivers.Out` port enumeration
#     ‚Ä¢ Typed `midi.FindInPort(name)` /  `FindOutPort(name)`
#       fuzzy-name port resolvers
#     ‚Ä¢ Typed `port.Send(msg Message)` /  `port.Open()` /
#       `port.Close()` typed port handle methods
#     ‚Ä¢ Typed `midi.NewListener(in)` /
#       `listener.OnEvery(receiver func(msg Message,
#       absms int32))` typed input-port subscription
#     ‚Ä¢ Typed `smf.ReadFrom(reader)` /  `smf.WriteTo(writer,
#       smfFile)` typed SMF I/O
#     ‚Ä¢ Typed Channel + Key constants ‚Äî every General MIDI
#       drum-kit slot (`drums.AcousticBassDrum = 35`,
#       `drums.BassDrum1 = 36`, `drums.SideStick = 37`,
#       `drums.AcousticSnare = 38`, `drums.HandClap = 39`,
#       `drums.ElectricSnare = 40`, ..., `drums.OpenSurdo =
#       87`), every standard CC number (`cc.ModulationWheel =
